1. Mac Books Introduction

This app provides a book trade system to Macalester students. The user can get a book at a lower price very quickly without having to wait for
a book to be shipped. The user can login into the system by using the google account and search for the book wanted, and get the seller information
so that they can contact each other. 

2. Procedures
2.1 You have to have a google account set up on your device to login into our system. To search for a book, click on the search bar on the main page.
You can put in the book ISBN number, the book title or the author name to search for the book. After the available books show up on the screen,
click on the book field for detailed information. If you decides to buy a book, click 'Buy' and send an e-mail to the seller to notify the seller 
that you want this book.

2.2 If you want to sell a book, click on the 'Sell Book' button, and you can input the book information including ISBN, the book title and the author name.
Then you can set the price of the book. It has to be at least 2 dollars. Click 'Search and Add', your book information will be stored in our database and 
show in the book list on the main page. 

2.3 Click on the 'My Profile' button, and it will show your personal information, including your name and e-mail address. At the bottom My Book List shows 
the books that you have input to sell. If you decide not to sell a book any more, click 'Delete Listing', and your book will be removed from our database.
Or if you decide to change the price, you can reset the price by clicking 'Edit Price'.


